resources.name: QX7 Open API v1.0
resources.description:
Welcome to the **QX7 Open API Documentation**, your gateway to a comprehensive repository of valuable information related to uniform styles, style components, brand details, and factory insights. With this API, you gain seamless access to a wealth of data that can significantly enhance your business operations within the apparel industry.

With the QX7 Open API, you can seamlessly integrate this wealth of information into your processes, empowering you to make data-driven decisions, streamline your operations, and stay at the forefront of the uniform and apparel industry. Unlock the potential of your business with our comprehensive documentation today.

The QX7 Open API is a secure and versatile interface designed to provide access to the QX7 platform's features and data. It allows authorized clients to interact with the QX7 ecosystem using client and secret keys for authentication. This API enables developers to integrate QX7's capabilities into their applications, services, or devices, fostering innovation and automation within the QX7 ecosystem.

#### Request Authentication
All requests should include this header to be able to authorize the requests.
This request should be using Content-Type = “application/json” with request header as below
```{
“QX-Client-Key”:””, 
“QX-Signature-Key”:””
} 
```
where:
- QX-Client-Key: Client Key - will be provided by PROLOOK QX7
- QX-Signature-Key: hash_hmac(‘sha256’, Client Key, Secret Key) – Client and Secret Key will be provided by PROLOOK QX7

For example, given these values:
- Client key: “abc123”
- Secret key: “123abc”

Then QX-Signature-Key = hash_hmac(‘sha256’, ‘abc123’, ‘123abc’)

QX-Signature-Key = E7239d81b67a18e48a1d57c1baa06b5d72a68973
```

}
```
